data.title: British Monarchs King Edward VII & Queen Alexandra of Denmark
data.meta_description:
Title -  King Edward VII and his Wife, Queen Alexandria
 
Description -  Edward VII (Born Albert Edward, November 9, 1841 - May 6, 1910), King of the United Kingdom and the British Dominions and Emperor of India from January 22, 1901 until his death in 1910.  He is pictured with his wife, Alexandra of Denmark (December 1, 1844 - November 20, 1925).
 
Description Source -  Bio from Wikipedia
 
Year -  Unknown
data.text:
The quality of historic images are subject to the capabilities of the original photographer, the wearing of time and the limitations of period technology. As history affords no retakes, we appreciate what has been left to us. Please note that we do not computer enhance or alter the original image in any way, as we feel its eccentricities contribute to its historic character. Thank you for taking this into consideration before making your purchase.

Sepia tone is available as an alternative to black and white. Color prints are also available in either black and white or sepia. There is no additional charge for this service. If you would like a tone different from the one pictured, please contact us after placing your order. Your print will arrive in the tone pictured unless otherwise instructed.
